Sniper: generally uses a sniper variant, carries a pistol sidearm, and a few magazines{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/58/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/58/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-2Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-2Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Plate Carrier: a Plate Carrier is a very common and efficient way to carry gear. They are covered in M.O.L.L.E. webbing which allows the user to put M.O.L.L.E. pouches anywhere they want. Plate carriers can be expensive. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3f/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3f/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cross draw  Vest: Cross draw vests generally have all the pouches sewn onto them. It is common for them to have a zipper in the middle for easy removal. These types of tactical vests are probably the most common vest in use by Airsofters. They are also relatively cheap, and can be found relatively easy online. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/39/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/39/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Harness & Battle belt: Commonly used by snipers Harness' and Battle belts, have a belt that attaches around the waist and can have M.O.L.L.E. pouches attached. They are often lightweight and can be worn with a Ghillie suit. The Harness has suspender like straps that help distribute the weight to the shoulders. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Choose-an-Airsoft-Vest-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
